<p>Data breaches and privacy concerns often dominate headlines, leaving both retail brands and consumers feeling vulnerable. Consumers are more conscious than ever about how their data is being used, which means retailers must not only secure that data but prove to customers that they can be trusted with it. Consumer data is a valuable asset, enabling personalized shopping experiences, better marketing, and improved customer satisfaction, but handling large amounts of personal data comes with real responsibility. Mishandling it, or a breach, can lead to financial losses, legal exposure, and lasting damage to a brand's reputation. Retailers need technology that safeguards customer data as a core part of their operations and infrastructure, not an afterthought.</p>

<h2>Adopting secure CRM</h2>
<p>Consumer data is often stored in CRM tools, which makes securing that layer especially important. A secure CRM lets retailers build a single source of information around each customer, gaining insight into behavior and purchasing habits across every channel while keeping personal information protected. Teamwork Commerce Secure CRM uses a high level of security to protect customer data and stays compliant with the evolving data regulations in Europe and the US. It adheres to these regulations through tokenization, replacing sensitive data with unique identification tokens to reduce the risk of data theft during a transaction. Teamwork Commerce has also achieved SOC 2 Type 2, a widely trusted accreditation that serves as a benchmark for a company's ability to safeguard client data, backed by comprehensive security measures around data security, availability, and confidentiality.</p>

<h2>Securing payment systems</h2>
<p>Alongside secure CRM, retailers need payment systems and gateways that are equally secure, both to complete transactions safely and to build consumer confidence. That means adhering to industry regulatory requirements and Payment Card Industry Data Security Standards, and considering biometric or multi-factor authentication as additional layers of protection for online transactions. In an omnichannel world where customers use a range of payment methods, Teamwork Commerce's Pay by Link solution, built in partnership with Adyen, lets customers pay for items through a secure URL link.</p>

<h2>Leveraging AI and machine learning</h2>
<p>Artificial intelligence and machine learning can meaningfully strengthen data privacy by identifying and mitigating threats in real time. AI-powered security systems can detect unusual patterns or behaviors that may indicate a breach, enabling faster action to prevent unauthorized access, while AI algorithms can analyze large volumes of data to identify vulnerabilities and anticipate future threats before they materialize.</p>

<h2>Protecting customer trust</h2>
<p>At a time when consumer data privacy is paramount, retailers need the right technology to protect their customers' information. Deploying technology that genuinely safeguards consumer privacy lets retailers both comply with regulation and reinforce the trust that keeps customers coming back.</p>
